text: Gonnesa (Gonnèsa) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sud Sardegna in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 5,033 people lived there. Its area is 48.06 km². It is 40 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of South Sardinia
title: Gonnesa
